Subject:[bcp] Philly Bike Expo
The third annual Philadelphia Bike Expo, which took place yesterday and tod=
ay at the Armory Building on 23rd Street, was another enjoyable and success=
ful event for local cyclists and bike clubs!=A0 There were great bargains o=
n all types of bicycle-related merchandise, as well as cycling-themed semin=
ars and clinics on a wide range of topics.
=A0
This event drew visitors (and exhibitors)=A0from a wide radius outside of P=
hiladelphia.
=A0
BCP's and SCU's tents were side by side, and it was alot of fun for our two=
 clubs to coolaborate.=A0 The Bicycle Coalition of Greater Philadelphia was=
 next door, and Neighborhood Bike Works also had a display table nearby.
=A0
Many thanks to everyone who volunteered at the BCP booth.=A0 We met scores =
of visitors, promoted all the rides, hikes, and activities and events BCP p=
rovides, signed up new members, welcomed renewing members, and sold merchan=
dise.
=A0
Friday evening set-up: John Siemiarowski, Vince Calkins, and Brian from the=
 Coalition.
=A0
Saturday: Howard Hochheiser, Jim Ruddick, and Vince Calkins.

Sunday: Lou Del Quadro, Laura Kelly, Ken Kress, Claire Scott, Vince Calkins=
, and Jeff Diacik.
